    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.796/740</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Canadian Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>With its memorandum of February 7th the Canadian Embassy enclosed copies of a
                    memorandum outlining the matters which, in the view of the Canadian Government,
                    might fall within the scope of a multilateral air transport convention.</p>
                <p>Enclosed for the confidential information of the United States Government are
                    eight copies of the draft of such a convention.<note n="53" xml:id="d322fn53"
                        >For text of the draft international air transport convention, see Canada,
                            <hi rend="italic">House of Commons Debates</hi>, vol. 82, No. 33, pp.
                        1626–1633.</note> This draft is a tentative and provisional statement of the
                    policy of the Canadian Government.</p>
                <p>The Canadian Government is most anxious to receive at an early date the
                    preliminary views of the United States Government on the general subject of
                    postwar civil aviation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-11">March 11,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
